              <p>
                When the detergent dispenser doesn’t open, it might be due to a
                broken dispenser door, faulty bi-metal actuator, or control
                board issues. A dispenser door that’s stuck or damaged can
                prevent detergent from being released. The bi-metal actuator,
                which triggers the dispenser door, might be malfunctioning.
                Issues with the control board can also disrupt the dispensing
                cycle. Inspecting and replacing these parts can ensure detergent
                is dispensed correctly for effective cleaning.
              </p>
            </div>

