                <div class="questions">
                  <p>
                    When your dishwasher isn't cleaning dishes effectively, it
                    could be due to several common issues. Here are a few
                    potential causes and solutions:
                  </p>
                  <ol>
                    <li>
                      <b>Clogged Filter or Spray Arm: </b> Over time, food particles
                      and debris can clog the filter or spray arm, reducing the appliance's
                      cleaning efficiency. To fix this, remove the filter and spray
                      arm and clean them thoroughly. Regular maintenance of these
                      small appliances within your dishwasher can prevent such issues.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Improper Loading: </b> Loading dishes incorrectly can block
                      the spray arms and prevent water from reaching all the dishes.
                      Ensure that larger items do not obstruct the spray arms and
                      that small appliances like cups and utensils are correctly
                      placed.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Using the Wrong Soap: </b> Using soap that is not specifically
                      designed for dishwashers can lead to residue buildup and poor
                      cleaning performance. Make sure to use dishwasher detergent
                      and avoid regular dish soap. It's also important to use the
                      correct amount of soap as instructed by the appliance manufacturer.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Water Temperature Issues: </b> Dishwashers typically require
                      water to be at a certain temperature to clean effectively.
                      Check your water heater settings to ensure it is set to the
                      temperature recommended by the appliance manufacturer. Running
                      hot water in the sink before starting the dishwasher can also
                      help.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <b>Malfunctioning Components: </b> If you've checked the above
